    "name": "CFD model credibly predicts absolute hemolysis index below clinical threshold for Class III VAD",
    "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump operating as a Class III VAD, produces absolute hemolysis index predictions that are credible for regulatory decision-making. Across all five flow-speed operating points, predicted hemolysis index values remain below the absolute clinical threshold of 0.8 g/dL per 100 mL, with Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds confirming that the 95th-percentile prediction does not exceed the threshold. The claim scope covers steady-state operating conditions at nominal blood viscosity and hematocrit, using the power-law hemolysis model with coefficients calibrated to Wurzinger et al. (1986) shear-exposure data.",
    "scope": "Steady-state operating envelope; five flow-speed combinations; nominal blood properties; FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry",
    "purpose": "Support regulatory submission demonstrating hemolysis safety for Class III VAD pre-market approval"
  },
