    "rationale": "Despite seven credibility factors achieving levels below required levels and six factors not assessed, the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification demonstrates that 95th-percentile hemolysis index predictions remain below the absolute clinical threshold at all five operating points. The assessment team accepted the package on the basis of the hemolysis claim and UQ results, noting that the claim is supported by ValidationResults with full provenance to experimental and computational evidence datasets. The orphan structure of the claim node — lacking a direct prov:wasDerivedFrom link to evidence — was not flagged during review, as the ValidationResults were presumed to transitively support the claim.",
